### What are HTTP methods?

💬 **Chat Explanation:**
> **Student**: "What's the difference between GET and POST?"
> 
> **Mentor**: "Think of it like CRUD operations in a library system:"
> - 📖 **GET** = Go and READ a book (no changes)
> - ✍️ **POST** = ADD a new book to the library
> - 📝 **PUT** = COMPLETELY REWRITE a book's info
> - 🗑️ **DELETE** = REMOVE a book from library
> - 🔧 **PATCH** = FIX only a few pages of a book

#### HTTP Methods Diagram:

```
┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    HTTP METHODS (CRUD)                         │
├────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│                                                                │
│  GET (Read)           POST (Create)     PUT (Update)   DELETE  │
│  ────────             ────────          ────────       ──────  │
│  Purpose:             Purpose:          Purpose:       Purpose:│
│  Fetch data           Create new        Replace        Remove  │
│  No body              Submit data       entire         data    │
│  Safe & Idempotent    resource          resource               │
│                                         Idempotent     Idempotent│
│                                                                │
│  Example:             Example:          Example:       Example:│
│  GET /users           POST /users       PUT /users/1   DELETE  │
│  GET /products/1      POST /orders      PUT /products/5 /users/1│
│                                                                │
│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │
│  │ PATCH (Partial Update)                                  │  │
│  │ Purpose: Update only specific fields                    │  │
│  │ Example: PATCH /users/1 { "email": "new@email.com" }   │  │
│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │
│                                                                │
└────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

KEY DIFFERENCE:
PUT replaces EVERYTHING  →  PATCH changes ONLY specified fields

PUT:   { "name": "John", "age": 30, "city": "NYC" }
       (Replaces entire user)

PATCH: { "age": 31 }
       (Only updates age, name & city remain same)
```

- **GET** – Retrieve data (Read)
- **POST** – Create data (Create)
- **PUT** – Update/Replace entire data (Update)
- **DELETE** – Delete data (Delete)
- **PATCH** – Partially update data (Partial Update)

