### What is an HTTP status code?

💬 **Chat Explanation:**
> **Student**: "Why do we need status codes?"
> 
> **Mentor**: "Status codes are like feedback from the server! They tell you what happened with your request."
> - ✅ 2xx = Success! Everything is good
> - ❓ 3xx = Redirect! Go somewhere else
> - ❌ 4xx = Client error! You did something wrong
> - 💥 5xx = Server error! The server has a problem

#### HTTP Status Codes Diagram:

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    HTTP STATUS CODES                            │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│                                                                 │
│  2xx - SUCCESS (Everything is Great!)                           │
│  ├─ 200 OK → Request successful, data returned                 │
│  ├─ 201 Created → New resource created (POST)                  │
│  └─ 204 No Content → Request successful, no data returned      │
│                                                                 │
│  3xx - REDIRECT (Go Somewhere Else!)                            │
│  ├─ 301 Moved Permanently → Resource moved to new URL          │
│  └─ 302 Found → Temporary redirect                             │
│                                                                 │
│  4xx - CLIENT ERROR (Your Fault!)                               │
│  ├─ 400 Bad Request → Malformed request                        │
│  ├─ 401 Unauthorized → Authentication failed (no login)        │
│  ├─ 403 Forbidden → Authenticated but no permission            │
│  ├─ 404 Not Found → Resource doesn't exist                     │
│  └─ 429 Too Many Requests → Rate limit exceeded                │
│                                                                 │
│  5xx - SERVER ERROR (Server's Fault!)                           │
│  ├─ 500 Internal Server Error → Server crashed                 │
│  ├─ 502 Bad Gateway → Upstream server error                    │
│  ├─ 503 Service Unavailable → Server is down/overloaded        │
│  └─ 504 Gateway Timeout → Server took too long                 │
│                                                                 │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

Real-World Example:
You order pizza (Request) → Server responds with status code:
├─ 200 → "Pizza is ready! Here you go!"
├─ 404 → "We don't have that topping!"
├─ 401 → "Please pay first!"
├─ 500 → "Our oven is broken, try again later!"
└─ 429 → "You're ordering too fast, wait a minute!"
```

It shows the result of the request:
- **200**: OK (Success)
- **201**: Created (New resource created)
- **400**: Bad Request (Invalid input)
- **401**: Unauthorized (Authentication failed)
- **403**: Forbidden (No permission)
- **404**: Not Found (Resource doesn't exist)
- **429**: Too Many Requests (Rate limit exceeded)
- **500**: Server Error (Backend problem)

