### What are RESTful APIs?

💬 **Chat Explanation:**
> **Student**: "What makes an API 'RESTful'?"
> 
> **Mentor**: "REST = Representational State Transfer. It's just fancy words for 'following standard rules'. A RESTful API follows principles like:"
> - Using HTTP methods correctly (GET for read, POST for create, etc.)
> - Resources have unique URLs
> - No state is stored on server (stateless)
> - Everything is about resources

APIs that follow REST (Representational State Transfer) principles using standard HTTP methods like GET, POST, PUT, DELETE.

#### RESTful API Example Diagram:

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│              RESTful API Design Example                         │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│                                                                 │
│  Base URL: https://api.example.com/v1                           │
│                                                                 │
│  USERS RESOURCE:                                                │
│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │
│  │ GET /users              → Get all users                 │   │
│  │ GET /users/1            → Get specific user (id=1)      │   │
│  │ POST /users             → Create new user               │   │
│  │ PUT /users/1            → Update entire user            │   │
