### What are headers in API?

💬 **Chat Explanation:**
> **Student**: "What are headers? Are they important?"
> 
> **Mentor**: "Think of headers like envelopes in postal mail! 📮 The envelope contains metadata ABOUT the letter:"
> - From: (Who sent it?)
> - To: (Who receives it?)
> - Type: (Letter, package, express?)
> - Weight: (How heavy?)
> 
> **API Headers work the same way:**

#### Headers Diagram:

```
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│         REQUEST with HEADERS                        │
├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│                                                      │
│  GET /users HTTP/1.1                                │
│  Host: api.example.com                              │
│  Content-Type: application/json                     │
│  Authorization: Bearer token123xyz                  │
│  Accept-Language: en-US                             │
│  User-Agent: Postman/10.0                           │
│                                                      │
│  (Body would come here if needed)                   │
│                                                      │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

COMMON HEADERS:
├─ Content-Type → What format? (JSON, XML, HTML)
├─ Authorization → Who are you? (API Key, Bearer Token)
├─ Accept → What do you want back?
├─ User-Agent → What app sent this?
├─ Content-Length → How big is the data?
├─ Accept-Language → What language?
└─ Cache-Control → Should we cache this?
```

Metadata passed in API requests/responses (e.g., Content-Type, Authorization).

