## QUICK CHEAT SHEET

### HTTP Methods Quick Reference

```
METHOD  | OPERATION | IDEMPOTENT | USE CASE
--------|-----------|------------|------------------------------------------
GET     | READ      | ✓ Yes      | Fetch data (no side effects)
POST    | CREATE    | ✗ No       | Create new resources
PUT     | REPLACE   | ✓ Yes      | Replace entire resource
PATCH   | MODIFY    | ✗ No       | Partial update
DELETE  | REMOVE    | ✓ Yes      | Delete resource
HEAD    | READ      | ✓ Yes      | Like GET but no body
OPTIONS | METADATA  | ✓ Yes      | Describe communication options
```

### Status Code Cheat Sheet

```
1xx - INFORMATIONAL
  100 Continue
  101 Switching Protocols

2xx - SUCCESS ✓
  200 OK
  201 Created
  204 No Content

3xx - REDIRECT
  301 Moved Permanently
  302 Found
  304 Not Modified

4xx - CLIENT ERROR ✗
  400 Bad Request
  401 Unauthorized
  403 Forbidden
  404 Not Found
  429 Too Many Requests

5xx - SERVER ERROR
  500 Internal Server Error
  502 Bad Gateway
  503 Service Unavailable
  504 Gateway Timeout
```

### Common Headers

```
HEADER                | PURPOSE
----------------------|-----------------------------------------------
Content-Type          | Format of data (application/json, text/xml)
Authorization         | Authentication token/credentials
Accept                | Expected response format
Accept-Language       | Preferred language
User-Agent            | Client application info
Cache-Control         | Caching instructions
Content-Length        | Size of request/response body
X-RateLimit-Limit     | Total requests allowed per period
X-RateLimit-Remaining | Requests remaining
Retry-After           | Wait time before retry (for 429/503)
CORS-Origin           | Cross-origin request origin
```

